# Agent Contract

This document is the binding contract for every agent operating on this project's `.memex/` tree. Hooks shipped by the [Memex](https://github.com/anthril/claude-memex) plugin enforce the contract at tool-call time — writes that violate it are blocked with a clear stderr message.

## 1. Before starting work

1. Read the README for the surface you're touching
2. Check `.open-questions/` for the topic; resolve or link before proceeding
3. Check `.audits/` (if the profile uses them) for prior findings
4. Read relevant rules under `.rules/`

## 2. Where documents live

See [README.md](README.md) for the folder map and [`../memex.config.json`](../memex.config.json) for the authoritative schema (`allowedTopLevel`, `readmeRequired`, `frontmatter.required`).

## 3. Required artifacts

| Trigger | Required doc |
|---|---|
| <!-- profile-specific: fill in from the profile's AGENTS.md --> | |

All artifacts require YAML frontmatter with at minimum: `title`, `slug`, `type`, `status`, `owner`, `created`, `updated`.

## 4. Forbidden actions

- Writing docs outside the taxonomy declared in `memex.config.json`
- Bypassing hooks (no `--no-verify`-style workarounds)
- Leaving `TODO` / `TBD` / `XXX` / `FIXME` markers inline — promote them to `.open-questions/` or a scoped `## Open questions` section
- Timestamps with colons or spaces (colons break Windows NTFS)
- Editing `.state/` by hand — it's plugin-managed session state

## 5. Escalation

If a rule seems wrong or too strict, file an entry in `.open-questions/` with the proposed change and rationale. Do not disable the hook.

